Company Overview of Oman Oil Marketing Company SAOG



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Oman Oil Marketing Company SAOG markets and distributes fuel and lubricant products primarily in the Sultanate of Oman. It operates through Retail, Commercial, and Others segments. The company operates a network of approximately 179 retail stations. It operates service station facilities, which comprise Ahlain stores, which offer cold drinks and hot snacks, top up groceries, milk, and phone cards; Lubeplus car services; and car wash services. The company also offers fuel cards; operates and manages semi-automated terminal for handling super motor spirit, regular motor spirit, diesel, and jet fuel; and operates a fleet of Jet A-1 aircraft refueling vehicles comprising various articulated tank...
Oman Oil Marketing Company SAOG markets and distributes fuel and lubricant products primarily in the Sultanate of Oman. It operates through Retail, Commercial, and Others segments. The company operates a network of approximately 179 retail stations. It operates service station facilities, which comprise Ahlain stores, which offer cold drinks and hot snacks, top up groceries, milk, and phone cards; Lubeplus car services; and car wash services. The company also offers fuel cards; operates and manages semi-automated terminal for handling super motor spirit, regular motor spirit, diesel, and jet fuel; and operates a fleet of Jet A-1 aircraft refueling vehicles comprising various articulated tankers and trailer combinations supplying jet fuel, aviation gasoline 100 LL, and lubricants to various sectors of the aviation industry. In addition, it engages in the supply of bulk petroleum products to various government and commercial customers and businesses; and bunkering marine fuels business. The company was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Mina Al Fahal, the Sultanate of Oman.
Detailed Description


