Oman Oil Marketing SAOG : EXECUTIVE MOVEMENTS 



































0






07/30/2017 | 04:27pm CEST 


Send by mail :
Last Name :
Name :
From* :
To* :
(You can enter multiple email addresses separated by commas)
Message :
*Required fields






Oman Oil Marketing Company, and its Board of Directors, recently welcomed David Kalife as CEO. In his role Kalife will oversee the company’s ongoing expansion strategy, the continued development of its bunker and trading capabilities, in addition to implementing its long-term strategies to increase in-country value and drive the sustainable growth of the company.

A French national, Kalife’s extensive professional background includes over a decade of experience in leadership roles. During his 21 years at oil giant Total S.A., Kalife earned a reputation for promoting a culture of innovation, continuous improvement and customer care by managing complexity in a consistent way and developing people. Beyond growth David Kalife believes in sustainability. During his years at Total, he oversaw the launch of new products such as the state-of-the-art Total Excellium in the South West Pacific market in addition to sealing successful partnerships in the Middle East with Hitachi Construction Machinery, AW Rostamani Trading, and KIA Motors among others.

Kalife is a graduate of the prestigious INSEAD. A keen humanitarian, he is also a founding member and former president of Fleur de Bitume, one of France’s effective charitable associations.

Infoline has appointed Mohammed Hamed Al Maskari as their new CEO. With over 25 years of senior management experience, Maskari brings along a wealth of industry experience to his new role in further developing the company’s vision into new markets, organic growth, strategic initiatives and strategy for expanding Infoline’s presence in Oman and the region and delivering added value to company’s investors.

In his previous roles, Maskari held various executive positions. His last engagement was as the director general of Knowledge Oasis Muscat. Prior to this he was heading the Information Center, Public Establishment for Industrial Estates (PEIE) supervising all the ICT applications and as a software developer in one of the leading IT Company called Oman Information Technology (OITC).

He is on the board of Oman Telecommunication Company and has served as a board director in The Research Council (TRC) from 2005 till 2016. He was also appointed as the regional president of the West Asia and North Africa, WANA in the International Association of Science Park and area of innovation, IASP 2012-2014. He holds Masters in Business Administration from Bedfordshire, UK and received his Bachelor’s degree in science from the Sultan Qaboos University.

Al Mouj Muscat has appointed Saleh Al Siyabi as vice president of Sales. Al Siyabi joined Al Mouj Muscat as early as 2006 when it first started and grew along with the company in the field of property sales.

During his professional career, Al Siyabi has attended many leadership and management programmes and comes well equipped with knowledge and skills required to lead the sales teams of Al Mouj Muscat.

Previously Al Siyabi has worked as an associate sales and marketing director at the Grand Hyatt Muscat and started his career in 1997 at Sheraton Oman Hotel as a sales manager.
He has a bachelor’s degree with honours in Marketing Management and a Master of Business Administration from University of Hull in the UK. Al Siyabi comes with more than 19 years of experience in the fields of sales, marketing, and customer service in the real estate development and hospitality sectors.(c) 2017 United Press & Publishing LLC Provided by SyndiGate Media Inc. (Syndigate.info)., source Middle East & North African Newspapers




















































